      "source": [
        "x = data.drop(\"label\", axis=1)\n",
        "y = data[\"label\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "display(x.head())\n",
        "display(y.head())"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pMv7AiXKEHos"
      },
      "source": [
        "Now we standarize our data."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 13,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mXtYNGMSqrVr",
        "outputId": "9ef0bdac-02d7-46ec-bcf4-daaccfe2ae99",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "array([-0.31633394, -0.31633394, -0.31633394, ..., -0.31633394,\n",
              "       -0.31633394, -0.31633394])"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 13
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler().fit(x)\n",
        "X = scaler.transform(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "X[0]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YrWufsE0qrVr"
      },
      "source": [
        "We split our data into train and test datasets."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 14,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WffqsKn7qrVt",
        "outputId": "6ed21530-f547-455b-d5da-01a42477611a",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "X shape: (1638, 2352)\n",
            "X_train shape: (1146, 2352)\n",
            "X_test shape: (492, 2352)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"X shape: {X.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"X_train shape: {X_train.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"X_test shape: {X_test.shape}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jJW168gMEtte"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Predictive modelling"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ppGPbusGPIUf"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Set up a baseline\n",
        "\n",
        "In order to assess correctly our model, we first need something to compare with. Absolute metrics have little meaning without a context. To this end it is quite common to apply a dumb forecasting just to have an estimation of the magnitude of the metrics. In our case we will always predict the most frequent class."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 15,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BWtaKvl0qrVv"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\n",
        "\n",
        "dummy_clf = DummyClassifier(strategy=\"most_frequent\")\n",
        "dummy_clf.fit(X, y)\n",
        "y_model = dummy_clf.predict(X_test)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 16,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BeImRvYDqrVw",
        "outputId": "df6344b1-2489-4e3e-fc67-658419c317f8",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "0.08943089430894309"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 16
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "accuracy_score(y_test, y_model)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 17,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nwwuD5LyqrVw",
        "outputId": "d19c8b18-9582-44de-c486-9bb3e9953390",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "array(['Earth', 'Earth', 'Earth', 'Earth', 'Earth', 'Earth', 'Earth',\n",
              "       'Earth', 'Earth', 'Earth'], dtype='<U5')"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 17
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "y_model[:10]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "97KKUEr0qrVx"
      },
      "source": [
        "This dummy classifier always classifies its input as 'Earth'. Now we are going to train several types of classifiers trying to improve our baseline accuracy; this is a standard practice in Machine Learning, remember that the No Free Lunch Theorem says that *a priori* we do not know which learning algorithm will perforn better.\n",
        "\n",
        "We will use accuracy as metric, given that it is a pretty standard classification task with a balanced dataset."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PfzuISmRqrVx"
      },
      "source": [
        "#### K-NN classifier\n",
        "\n",
        "Model fit:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 20,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kym1q5ojqrVx"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier\n",
        "\n",
        "modelKNN = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5)\n",
        "modelKNN.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "y_model_knn_og = modelKNN.predict(X_test)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mkDySjWIqrVy"
      },
      "source": [
        "Model evaluation:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 21,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "k4KtxBzWqrVy",
        "outputId": "4d754fc5-95a2-4220-c59d-9ba9a51c6c26",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "0.975609756097561"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 21
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
        "\n",
        "results = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "results['knn'] = accuracy_score(y_test, y_model_knn_og)\n",
        "results['knn']"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Jiim_WwHqrVy"
      },
      "source": [
        "#### Support Vector Machine (SVM) classifier"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 22,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EOTKJ6L-qrVy"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
        "\n",
        "modelSVC = SVC(C=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "modelSVC.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "y_model_svc_og = modelSVC.predict(X_test)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 23,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KlVTttBiqrVz",
        "outputId": "9324821f-2fa5-498a-febd-5e4abf77a020",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "0.9410569105691057"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 23
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "results['svm'] = accuracy_score(y_test, y_model_svc_og)\n",
        "results['svm']"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ynzUXlBSqrVz"
      },
      "source": [
        "#### Classification tree"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 24,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NAIZyYHuqrVz"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\n",
        "\n",
        "modelTree = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=None)\n",
        "modelTree.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "y_model_tree_og = modelTree.predict(X_test)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 25,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sVObkhD7qrV0"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "results['tree'] = accuracy_score(y_test, y_model_tree_og)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2odc_iOGqrV0"
      },
      "source": [
        "Finally, we compare the accuracy of our models:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 26,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9OaFO11OqrV0",
        "outputId": "8aba7c1d-5c2b-4604-c268-54344eff95b1",
